docs.abstract: Department store customers, taking advantage of returns policies set by retailers competing with e-commerce, are playing havoc with sales commissions.
docs.snippet: Department store customers, taking advantage of returns policies set by retailers competing with e-commerce, are playing havoc with sales commissions.
docs.lead_paragraph: Earnestine Gay, a longtime worker in the fragrance department at Macy’s in Herald Square, clearly remembers a bottle of perfume that was returned recently. It was practically empty.

headline.main: Liberal Return Policies for Consumers Can Reduce Retail Workers’ Pay
headline.print_headline: The Sting of a Liberal Retail Returns Policy

docs.abstract: A Nielsen study on how we consume media finds people are still watching plenty of TV but services like Netflix and Amazon Prime are growing rapidly.
docs.snippet: A Nielsen study on how we consume media finds people are still watching plenty of TV but services like Netflix and Amazon Prime are growing rapidly.
docs.lead_paragraph: You still love television. You use your tablet more than ever. And now you are as likely to have paid services like Netflix or Amazon Prime as you are to have a DVR service.

headline.main: How Much Do We Love TV? Let Us Count the Ways
headline.print_headline: How Much Do We Love Television? Let Us Count the Ways

docs.abstract: Our critics look at a few of the latest crop of original pilots. Viewers can watch and vote on their favorites.
docs.snippet: Our critics look at a few of the latest crop of original pilots. Viewers can watch and vote on their favorites.
docs.lead_paragraph: Since 2013, Amazon has released a batch of original TV pilots several times a year for the public to review and vote on. Our TV critics look at a few from the latest crop.

headline.main: Amazon’s Literary Forays for TV: ‘The Interestings’ and ‘The Last Tycoon’
